Description: FENDER made in japan HH triple black phat strat. black body total black neck and headstock, black hardware = Black Beauty. serial number research indicates it was made at the Fugi-gen Plant in Japan between 1985-86, big sound big hair days. i've had this stored in its case for several years but now it's time to thin out the pile. having not checked it out for all this time i'm amazed at how clean and how good it looks and sounds, showing minimal signs of use through out the instrument. no mentionable dings or serious scratches on body or neck, just normal pickguard marks. not positive but i seem to recall installing high end dimarzio pickups years back, look and sounds like it but i'm not about to tear her apart to find out, that would be up to new owner. the only original item missing is the locking string trem unit that attaches above the nut, kind of a pain in the butt, if you are a big whammy guy i'll check my parts to try and find. the trem bridge on these models is Fenders answer to floyd rose type locking trem with fine tuners, they work great, whammy away. zoom in on the 2 original volume/tone knobs and you'll see the rare F logo, these are usually gone. the 22 fret rosewood finger board is perfect, straight arrow, and shows little if any wear, minimal use and NO abuse on this baby. for being nearly 40 years seasoned, the only signs of age is some surface discoloration on the neck plate and that's where the serial number is located if you can see it in pix. she sleeps and ships in a Fender USA hard case from the 80s era as seen, handle, hinges and latches are all good, outside shows normal wear and some sticker residue, inside is super clean. it's been set up and dialed in, ready to rock. buyer adds $25.00 to help with ever rising shipping costs and i'll cover the rest going to mainland 48 states only. selling as is with NO negative issues, sure to please the next player to get their hands on her, could be YOU! a high quality desirable insrument here, i DON'T DO junk. due to past bad experiences, PLEASE only bid if you intend to follow thru, THANX i appreciate your looks and bids. rock on friendshere's info i found on the net:serial number: A004131Guitar InfoYour guitar was made at the Fuji-gen Plant (for Fender Japan), Japanin 1985 - 1986Production Number: 4131 Fuji String Instrument Production CorporationFuji String Instrument Production Corporation was opened in may 1960, they initially started manufacturing violins and quickly switched to classical guitar production. In 1962 electric guitar construction was started. Fujigen has a reputation for excellent quality and craftsmanship so the guitars they produce are highly regarded. They produce guitars via OEM for famous brands such as Ibanez, Epiphone, Yamaha and Fender (the import Special Interest Group nature model), G&L and others.
